  "prompt": "Why does Facebook keep on disabling any account I create even before I could have the option to upload a profile photo?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why Facebook might be disabling your accounts:\n\n1. Suspected duplicate accounts\n- Facebook's system might detect you're creating multiple accounts from the same device/IP address\n\n2. Potential violation of their terms of service\n- Using fake names\n- Creating accounts with suspicious information\n- Being underage\n\n3. Automated security systems\n- Detecting potential bot or spam account creation\n- Unusual account creation patterns\n\n4. Previous account history\n- If a previous account was banned or violated community standards\n- Using the same device/IP address associated with a banned account\n\n5. Location-based restrictions\n- Some regions have stricter account creation policies\n\nRecommendations:\n- Use a genuine, verifiable identity\n- Ensure you're using a unique IP address\n- Verify your phone number or email\n- Wait between account creation attempts\n- Ensure you meet Facebook's age requirements\n- Contact Facebook support for specific details\n\nIf the issue persists, you might want to contact Facebook directly for more precise information about why your accounts are being disabled.",
